69102::$$$message_0633_0000_0000$$$::   I have to use Archer's arm.[lr]::
69103::$$$message_0633_0000_0001$$$::I can't let Rider do this.[lr]::
69104::$$$message_0633_0000_0002$$$::Either I surpass my Projection limits, or she'll kill me. It's do or die!::
69105::$$$message_0633_0001_0000$$$::[font italic=true]"Trace, on. (Begin Projection.)"[font italic=false][lr]::
69106::$$$message_0633_0001_0001$$$::I start up my Magic Circuits, keeping my eyes on Rider.[lr]::
69107::$$$message_0633_0001_0002$$$::...I won't Project my weapons until the last possible second.[lr]::
69108::$$$message_0633_0001_0003$$$::The instant Rider moves towards me, I'll create a sword in zero seconds flat and intercept her with all my might!::
69109::$$$message_0633_0002_0000$$$::"...Projection magecraft. I cannot use you to your full potential, but an excellent swordsman might be able to best utilize you as a Noble Phantasm."::
69110::$$$message_0633_0003_0000$$$::"...?"[lr]::
69111::$$$message_0633_0003_0001$$$::Rider's bloodlust recedes.[lr]::
69112::$$$message_0633_0003_0002$$$::She withdraws, as if she's read my mind.::
69113::$$$message_0633_0004_0000$$$::"...Rider?"[lr]::
69114::$$$message_0633_0004_0001$$$::"I will let you go. I cannot use you.[lr]::
69115::$$$message_0633_0004_0002$$$::...What an ironic twist of fate, Shirou. If Saber were still here, she would be an ideal partner for you."::
69116::$$$message_0633_0005_0000$$$::Rider's presence fades away.[lr]::
69117::$$$message_0633_0005_0001$$$::She must have left the house right away after she came out of the shed.[lr]::
69118::$$$message_0633_0005_0002$$$::Her bloodlust is gone, and it doesn't seem like it'll ever return.::
69119::$$$message_0633_0006_0000$$$::"..."[lr]::
69120::$$$message_0633_0006_0001$$$::Did she...let me go?[lr]::
69121::$$$message_0633_0006_0002$$$::Unless I'm imagining it, she might have offered to help me if I'd given her a chance...::

